22/04/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- State Minister Kursad Tuzmen and Romanian Economy Minister Dan Ioan Popescu signed an agreement Wednesday (21 April) boosting bilateral and regional economic co-operation.
The Turkey-Romania Joint Economic Commission protocol provides concrete measures to achieve targets in bilateral trade volume and investment.
Also Wednesday, Turkey and Bulgaria signed agreements on air and sea transportation.
Among them is an update to the 1966 Air Transportation Agreement, made in light of new security concerns.
(Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, NTV, BTA - 21/04/04)
